      "parameters": {
        "width": 720,
        "height": 1280,
        "content": "# üìä  Email Validation & Google Sheets Update\n\nThis workflow automates the process of validating email addresses stored in a Google Sheet. It reads each email, checks if it's disposable or fake using a third-party API (via RapidAPI), and updates the same row with the result. All interactions with Google Sheets are done securely using a Google Service Account.\n\n---\n\n## ‚úÖ Node-wise Overview\n\n### üîò Manual Trigger  \nStarts the workflow manually from the n8n editor.\n\n### üìÑ Google Sheets (Read)  \nReads all rows (including emails) from a specified Google Sheet.\n\n### üîÅ Split In Batches  \nProcesses each row (email) one at a time.\n\n### üåê HTTP Request (RapidAPI)  \nSends the email to a validation API via HTTP POST.\n\n### üü© Google Sheets (Update Row)  \nUpdates the corresponding row in the sheet with the validation result.\n\n---\n\n## üí° Use Cases\n\n- üìß **Email List Cleanup**  \n  Keep your lead or contact lists free of fake, temporary, or disposable emails.\n\n- üßº **Data Quality Enhancement**  \n  Ensure your Google Sheets contain only validated, high-quality email addresses.\n\n- üîÅ **Automated Data Enrichment**  \n  Add metadata (like `is_disposable`) to your contacts without manual review.\n\n- üì• **Lead Qualification Filtering**  \n  Automatically flag or remove junk leads before importing into CRMs or email tools.\n\n---"
      },
      "typeVersion": 1
